Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new intuitionistic substructural logic called ILGL and provides soundness and completeness theorems for a labelled tableaux system with respect to a Kripke semantics on graphs. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of models of complex systems in the physical and social sciences, which is relevant to AI research. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper mentions graph-theoretic structures and their use in modelling complex systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper discusses the semantics and proof theory of a logic system. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper discusses the utility of the logic system in a resource-labelled bigraph model, which could be relevant to software engineering.
